1) NodeJs and NPM. Just need to install NodeJs as NPM comes with it automaticcaly.
2) Git tool.
3) Meta mask chrome extension.
4) Remix online IDE - http://remix.ethereum.org(Can be used for quickly writing and testing smart contracts)

Following NPM modules needs to be installed.

-> ganache-cli(Test network) 
    npm install --save ganache-cli
-> solc(Solidity compiler) 
    npm install --save solc
-> mocha (JS testing framework)
    npm install --save mocha
-> web3(Java script API for interacting with ethereum network) -> Run following command as administractor
    npm install --global --production windows-build-tools
   And install following module, 
    npm install --save web3@1.0.0-beta.26
-> webpack  
    npm install --save webpack
-> Install Truffle provider to set up web3 to connect to different ethereum networks, 
    npm install --save truffle-hdwallet-provider
